By BO Staff Writer Annually on 1st January, Amabutho, Intsha and Iziboshwa gather at the President’s home in Nkandla, KwaZulu-Natal, to showcase their traditional dance talent. The picture seen below were taken at the 2018 celebration. Over 5000 youth came together as part of recreation, to dance before his Excellency President Zuma. This joint initiative between AmaNxamalala and the Jacob G. Zuma Foundation started in 2001. Five cows are slaughtered and people celebrate New Year’s day in style. President Zuma, the People’s President.      
  